This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it focuses on natural language understanding and grounding. It is also likely to belong to cs.RO (Robotics) because it deals with robots and their ability to understand natural language instructions. Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it involves probabilistic modeling and inference. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) because it incorporates visual observations into the model. Finally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it involves learning a state representation for a belief over factual groundings.
